  "body": "In profile section there are several options how PNs should be shown:\r\n\r\n1. anonymous\r\n2. name only\r\n3. name and message\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1012\" alt=\"Screenshot 2021-09-01 at 10 28 02\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/82375995/131630277-fed24c5d-158d-4bf0-a5f0-19e0cf88be41.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\nThe settings are not being taken into consideration, so when a desktop user receives a mention in a chat (lets say public chat), the incoming PN contains a chat key of the mentioned user, but not the name or name + text\r\n\r\n<img width=\"376\" alt=\"Screenshot 2021-09-01 at 10 18 21\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/82375995/131630436-a86ece9f-dd17-4a6b-8244-2c59a7970dc1.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\nHow to reproduce?\r\n\r\n**In notifications settings of desktop app select option 3: name and message** (but the issue is applicable to any of options selected)\r\n\r\n1. install an app to desktop\r\n2. install an app to mobile\r\n3. join the same public chat\r\n4. add each other to contacts\r\n5. collapse the desktop app so it is on background\r\n6. from mobile, in the public chat mention a user on desktop\r\n7. receive a push notification\r\n\r\n**Expected result:** push notification body contains the text that matches the setting selection, either anonymous, or name only or name and message\r\n\r\n**Version:** `Version: 0.1.0-beta.11 , master Build #1294 (31-Aug-2021 19:18:57)`, MacOS Big Sur 11.5.2",
